---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Tally Alternative for Indian SMEs: Custom ERP vs Tally Prime (2026) | Softwaller";
const description = "Fair, factual comparison: Tally Prime vs custom ERP for Indian SMEs. When to switch, 5 outgrowing signs, 3-year cost comparison, migration plan, and the keep-Tally-add-modules option. 2026 guide.";
const canonical = "https://www.softwaller.com/compare/custom-erp-vs-tally.html";
const ogImage = "https://www.softwaller.com/assets/og-image.jpg";
const ogTitle = "Tally Alternative for Indian SMEs: Custom ERP vs Tally Prime (2026)";
const ogDescription = "Fair, factual comparison: Tally Prime vs custom ERP. When to switch, 3-year cost, migration plan, and the keep-Tally-add-modules option.";
const jsonLd = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 1,
        "name": "Home",
        "item": "https://www.softwaller.com/"
      },
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 2,
        "name": "Compare",
        "item": "https://www.softwaller.com/compare/"
      },
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 3,
        "name": "Custom ERP vs Tally"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Tally Alternative for Growing Indian SMEs — Custom ERP Comparison (2026)",
    "description": "Fair, factual comparison of Tally Prime vs custom ERP for Indian SMEs. When to switch, 5 outgrowing signs, 3-year cost comparison, migration plan.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Softwaller Technologies Private Limited",
      "url": "https://www.softwaller.com"
    },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Softwaller Technologies Private Limited",
      "logo": {
        "@type": "ImageObject",
        "url": "https://www.softwaller.com/assets/softwaller-technologies-logo-light.webp"
      }
    },
    "datePublished": "2026-04-26",
    "dateModified": "2026-04-26",
    "mainEntityOfPage": {
      "@type": "WebPage",
      "@id": "https://www.softwaller.com/compare/custom-erp-vs-tally.html"
    },
    "image": "https://www.softwaller.com/assets/og-image.jpg"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Tally bad for Indian SMEs?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. Tally Prime is excellent for accounting, GST returns, and statutory compliance — it is used by 2+ million Indian businesses for good reason. The question is not whether Tally is bad, it is whether Tally still fits your workflow as you scale beyond accounting into manufacturing, multi-branch operations, mobile sales, marketplace sales, or 50+ users with role-based workflows. Most SMEs outgrow Tally for those scenarios, not for accounting itself."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I switch from Tally?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Consider switching when at least 3 of these are true: (1) you export to Excel for every meaningful report, (2) salesmen book orders manually then re-key into Tally, (3) production data lives in WhatsApp Business chats and Excel, (4) multi-location stock visibility takes a phone call, (5) you are paying for 3+ Tally licenses plus 2+ third-party add-ons. These signal that workflow gaps now cost more than a custom ERP investment."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I keep Tally for accounting and add custom modules around it?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes — this is often the smartest path. Keep Tally Prime as your accounting and statutory backbone, and add custom modules for your real workflow gaps: a sales mobile app, production tracker, multi-branch stock dashboard, or a WhatsApp Business order intake. These modules sync data with Tally via XML, ODBC, or Tally Connector. You preserve your CA workflow and migrate only the parts that hurt."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does Tally to ERP migration take?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For a typical mid-market SME: 3–5 months for build, 2–3 months for parallel run, 1 month for cutover. End-to-end roughly 6–9 months. Master data migration (ledgers, items, parties, opening balances) is usually 4–6 weeks. We always recommend running Tally and the new ERP in parallel for at least 2 months before cutover."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What happens to my historical Tally data?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Two options. Option 1 (most common): keep your existing Tally Prime company data file as a read-only archive for 7+ years of historical access — it stays available for past returns, audits, and reference. Option 2: import opening balances, masters, and last 1–2 financial years into the custom ERP. We recommend a hybrid: archive Tally for past years, import current year opening balances into the new ERP."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Tally migration cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Migration scope drives cost: master data migration alone is typically ₹50,000–₹1,50,000. Full custom ERP build with Tally migration starts around ₹15 lakh and ranges to ₹30+ lakh for multi-branch, multi-module deployments. The 3-year TCO including AMC is generally 30–50% lower than equivalent SaaS ERP for mid-market businesses."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Will my CAs and accountants need to relearn?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "There is a learning curve, but a custom ERP can replicate Tally-like accounting screens (voucher entry, day book, ledger view) so accountants stay productive. If you choose the keep-Tally-add-modules path, accountants continue using Tally exactly as before — only operations and sales teams move to the new system. Most CAs adapt within 2–4 weeks of training."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} ogImage={ogImage} ogTitle={ogTitle} ogDescription={ogDescription} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <Fragment slot="head-css" set:html={`<link rel="stylesheet" href="../assets/product.min.css?v=1.0.3">`} />
  <style is:global slot="head-css" set:html={`
.faq-section{margin:48px 0 32px;padding:0}
.faq-section h2{font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:var(--ink);letter-spacing:-.5px;margin:0 0 18px}
.faq-section p.faq-sub{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:20px;line-height:1.7}
.faq-item{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:10px;background:var(--white);transition:border-color .2s}
.faq-item:hover{border-color:var(--blue-br)}
.faq-item[open]{border-color:var(--blue-br);box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(10,15,30,.06)}
.faq-item summary{padding:18px 22px;font-size:15.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);cursor:pointer;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:16px;line-height:1.5}
.faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker{display:none}
.faq-item summary::after{content:'\\002B';font-size:22px;font-weight:400;color:var(--blue);flex-shrink:0;transition:transform .2s}
.faq-item[open] summary::after{content:'\\2212'}
.faq-item .faq-answer{padding:0 22px 20px;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8}
.cmp-section{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:48px 28px}
.cmp-section h2{font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:var(--ink);letter-spacing:-.5px;margin:0 0 8px}
.cmp-section p.sub{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 24px;line-height:1.7}
.cmp-section h3{font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin:18px 0 8px}
.cmp-section p{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;margin:0 0 14px}
.cmp-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:16px;margin:18px 0}
.cmp-card{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;padding:20px;background:var(--white)}
.cmp-card h3{margin:0 0 8px;font-size:16px;color:var(--ink)}
.cmp-card p{font-size:14px;margin:0;color:var(--muted)}
.cmp-card .cmp-ic{width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:10px;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:12px;font-size:16px}
.cmp-table-wrap{overflow-x:auto;margin:18px 0;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;background:var(--white)}
.cmp-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:14px;min-width:640px}
.cmp-table th,.cmp-table td{padding:14px 16px;text-align:left;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);vertical-align:top}
.cmp-table th{background:var(--bg);font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);font-size:13.5px;letter-spacing:.2px}
.cmp-table tr:last-child td{border-bottom:0}
.cmp-table .cap{font-weight:700;color:var(--ink)}
.cmp-table .yes{color:#059669;font-weight:700}
.cmp-table .partial{color:#EA580C;font-weight:600}
.cmp-table .no{color:#9CA3AF}
.cmp-list{list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0}
.cmp-list li{padding:14px 16px 14px 44px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;background:var(--white);margin-bottom:10px;position:relative;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7}
.cmp-list li::before{content:counter(sign);counter-increment:sign;position:absolute;left:14px;top:14px;width:22px;height:22px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue);font-weight:800;font-size:12px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center}
.cmp-list{counter-reset:sign}
.cmp-list li strong{color:var(--ink)}
.cmp-stat-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:14px;margin:18px 0}
.cmp-stat{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:16px;background:var(--white)}
.cmp-stat .num{font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:var(--blue);letter-spacing:-.5px}
.cmp-stat .lbl{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:4px;line-height:1.5}
.cmp-step{display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start;padding:14px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.cmp-step:last-child{border-bottom:0}
.cmp-step .num{flex-shrink:0;width:34px;height:34px;border-radius:10px;background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:800;font-size:14px}
.cmp-step .body h3{margin:0 0 4px;font-size:15.5px;color:var(--ink)}
.cmp-step .body p{margin:0;font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7}
.cmp-callout{border:1px solid var(--blue-br);border-radius:14px;padding:20px;background:var(--blue-bg);margin:20px 0}
.cmp-callout h3{margin:0 0 8px;font-size:16px;color:var(--ink)}
.cmp-callout p{margin:0;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.7}
.cmp-tm{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.7;padding:18px 22px;border-top:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--bg)}
`}></style>
  <Fragment set:html={`
<section class="phero">
  <div class="phero-inner">
    <div class="phero-text">
      <div class="phero-icon" style="background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue)"><i class="fa-solid fa-scale-balanced"></i></div>
      <h1>Tally Alternative for Growing Indian SMEs — Custom ERP Comparison (2026)</h1>
      <p>Tally Prime is excellent for accounting, GST returns, and statutory compliance. But most Indian SMEs hit limits when they scale into multi-branch operations, manufacturing workflow, mobile sales, marketplace integration, or 50+ users. A custom ERP from Softwaller is the typical graduation path — and in many cases, the smarter choice is to <strong>keep Tally Prime as the accounting backbone and build custom modules around it</strong>. Below is a fair, factual comparison: what Tally does brilliantly, where it hits limits, the 3-year cost picture, and a step-by-step migration plan.</p>
      <p style="font-size:13.5px;margin-top:10px"><em>Independent comparison &middot; Trademark notice in footer &middot; Verify current vendor pricing on official sources before purchase decisions</em></p>
    </div>
    <div class="phero-visual">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><rect width="400" height="300" rx="16" fill="#fff" stroke="#E4E7F0" stroke-width="1.5"/><rect x="30" y="60" width="150" height="180" rx="12" fill="#FFF7ED" stroke="#FED7AA" stroke-width="1.5"/><text x="105" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="800" fill="#EA580C">Tally Prime</text><text x="105" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="#9A3412">Accounting · GST · CA-friendly</text><circle cx="60" cy="135" r="4" fill="#EA580C"/><text x="72" y="139" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#9A3412">GST Returns</text><circle cx="60" cy="158" r="4" fill="#EA580C"/><text x="72" y="162" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#9A3412">Day Book</text><circle cx="60" cy="181" r="4" fill="#EA580C"/><text x="72" y="185" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#9A3412">P&amp;L · Trial Bal</text><circle cx="60" cy="204" r="4" fill="#EA580C"/><text x="72" y="208" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#9A3412">Statutory</text><rect x="220" y="60" width="150" height="180" rx="12" fill="#EBF0FF" stroke="#C2CFFF" stroke-width="1.5"/><text x="295" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="14" font-weight="800" fill="#1557FF">Custom ERP</text><text x="295" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="#1E3A8A">Workflow · Mobile · Scale</text><circle cx="250" cy="135" r="4" fill="#1557FF"/><text x="262" y="139" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#1E3A8A">BOM &amp; MRP</text><circle cx="250" cy="158" r="4" fill="#1557FF"/><text x="262" y="162" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#1E3A8A">Multi-Branch</text><circle cx="250" cy="181" r="4" fill="#1557FF"/><text x="262" y="185" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#1E3A8A">Mobile Sales</text><circle cx="250" cy="204" r="4" fill="#1557FF"/><text x="262" y="208" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#1E3A8A">WhatsApp Biz</text><line x1="180" y1="150" x2="220" y2="150" stroke="#9CA3AF" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/><text x="200" y="145" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="#6B7280">XML/ODBC</text></svg>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cmp-section">
  <h2>The Honest Picture in Numbers</h2>
  <p class="sub">Four data points that frame this comparison. Tally Solutions is the dominant accounting software in India for very real reasons — and that's exactly why the question is rarely "should I leave Tally?" but rather "where do I extend beyond Tally?"</p>
  <div class="cmp-stat-row">
    <div class="cmp-stat"><div class="num">2 M+</div><div class="lbl">Indian businesses use Tally Solutions products (Tally Solutions official figures)</div></div>
    <div class="cmp-stat"><div class="num">Tiered</div><div class="lbl">Tally Prime publishes Silver (single-user) and Gold (multi-user) subscription tiers &mdash; refer to Tally Solutions' official pricing page for current rates</div></div>
    <div class="cmp-stat"><div class="num">Many</div><div class="lbl">Indian SMEs report exploring an ERP that goes beyond Tally as they scale into manufacturing or multi-branch operations (Softwaller engagement observations)</div></div>
    <div class="cmp-stat"><div class="num">30–50%</div><div class="lbl">Indicative lower 3-year TCO for a right-sized custom ERP vs equivalent SaaS for mid-market in our project experience — actual savings vary by scope and user count</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cmp-section" style="background:var(--bg);max-width:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0">
  <div style="max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2>What Tally Does Brilliantly</h2>
    <p class="sub">Before discussing limits, it's important to acknowledge what Tally Prime genuinely does better than most alternatives — including custom ERP. If you only need these things, Tally is the right tool and you should not change.</p>
    <div class="cmp-grid">
      <div class="cmp-card">
        <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green)"><i class="fa-solid fa-calculator"></i></div>
        <h3>Best-in-Class Accounting & GST</h3>
        <p>Voucher entry, day book, trial balance, P&amp;L, balance sheet, and GST returns (GSTR-1, GSTR-3B) are mature and battle-tested. Tally Prime handles edge cases — reverse charge, RCM, ITC reconciliation — with rigour built up over decades.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-card">
        <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue)"><i class="fa-solid fa-graduation-cap"></i></div>
        <h3>Easy for Accountants to Learn</h3>
        <p>Most Indian accountants and CAs already know Tally Prime. New hires are productive on day one. This is a quietly massive operational advantage that custom ERPs cannot replicate without explicit accounting-screen design.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-card">
        <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--orange-bg);color:var(--orange)"><i class="fa-solid fa-tag"></i></div>
        <h3>Affordable Entry Point</h3>
        <p>Tally Prime is published in Silver (single-user) and Gold (multi-user) tiers &mdash; refer to Tally Solutions' official pricing page for current rates. For businesses where Tally fits, the per-branch / per-licence economics are dramatically cheaper than commissioning custom development, particularly up to ~10 users.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-card">
        <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--purple-bg);color:var(--purple)"><i class="fa-solid fa-people-group"></i></div>
        <h3>Huge CA & Consultant Ecosystem</h3>
        <p>Every Indian city has Tally consultants, partners, and customisation experts. Returns filing, audits, and statutory submissions assume Tally. This network effect is real value, not just nostalgia.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-card">
        <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--cyan-bg);color:var(--cyan)"><i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i></div>
        <h3>Reliable, Mature Product</h3>
        <p>Tally Solutions Pvt Ltd has refined this product for over 30 years. Crashes are rare, data corruption rarer, and statutory updates ship reliably with each GST or compliance change.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-callout">
      <h3>Our honest position</h3>
      <p>If your business is a single-location trader with under 10 users, predominantly accounting-driven, and you don't have unique workflow requirements — <strong>stay on Tally Prime</strong>. Custom ERP is overkill and we'd tell you so on the first call. The rest of this page is for businesses that have outgrown that profile.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cmp-section">
  <h2>Where Tally Hits Its Ceiling</h2>
  <p class="sub">These are the specific scenarios where SMEs report Tally pain. None of them are flaws in Tally — they are simply outside its design intent. Tally is an accounting and inventory product, not a workflow ERP.</p>
  <div class="cmp-grid">
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--orange-bg);color:var(--orange)"><i class="fa-solid fa-gears"></i></div>
      <h3>Production & Manufacturing Workflow</h3>
      <p>Bill of Materials with multi-level routing, work orders, shop-floor tracking, machine-wise output, and MRP planning are not native to Tally. Add-ons exist but feel grafted on. A textile dyeing unit, plastic injection moulding plant, or precision engineering shop will outgrow this quickly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue)"><i class="fa-solid fa-building"></i></div>
      <h3>Multi-Branch & Multi-GSTIN Consolidation</h3>
      <p>Running 4 branches across 3 states with different GSTINs in Tally typically means 4 company files, manual consolidation in Excel, and reconciliation pain at month-end. Real-time multi-branch stock visibility and inter-branch transfers need workarounds.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--pink-bg);color:var(--pink)"><i class="fa-solid fa-diagram-project"></i></div>
      <h3>Custom Workflows by Industry</h3>
      <p>Textile yarn-lot tracking, jewellery RFID with making charges, real-estate inventory by tower-floor-flat, automotive serial-number traceability, food batch and expiry — these need data models Tally doesn't natively support.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--cyan-bg);color:var(--cyan)"><i class="fa-solid fa-mobile-screen"></i></div>
      <h3>Mobile-First Sales & Field Teams</h3>
      <p>A 30-person sales team taking orders at customer locations, a delivery boy capturing PoD, or a service engineer logging spares used — Tally doesn't ship a strong mobile experience. Salesmen end up booking on paper and re-keying into Tally at end of day.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--purple-bg);color:var(--purple)"><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line"></i></div>
      <h3>Custom Dashboards & Analytics</h3>
      <p>Tally reports are excellent for accounting but limited for business analytics. Owner dashboards showing live cash, pending collections, top customers, route-wise sales, and SKU-level margins typically end up in Excel exports rather than Tally itself.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green)"><i class="fa-brands fa-whatsapp"></i></div>
      <h3>WhatsApp Business Automation</h3>
      <p>Sending invoices, payment reminders, order status, and dispatch notifications via WhatsApp Business Cloud API requires integration that Tally does not provide natively. Most Indian customers prefer WhatsApp over email today.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--orange-bg);color:var(--orange)"><i class="fa-solid fa-cart-shopping"></i></div>
      <h3>Marketplace & Web Store Integration</h3>
      <p>Selling on Amazon, Flipkart, Meesho, or your own Shopify store needs two-way sync of orders, inventory, prices, and returns. Tally connectors exist but are typically third-party and patchy. Errors compound over time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--blue-bg);color:var(--blue)"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-double"></i></div>
      <h3>Custom Approval Workflows</h3>
      <p>Multi-level PO approval based on amount, branch, and category; credit-note approval by sales head and accounts; advance approval by directors — these workflow chains are not native in Tally and require manual oversight.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--pink-bg);color:var(--pink)"><i class="fa-solid fa-user-shield"></i></div>
      <h3>Role-Based Access for 50+ Users</h3>
      <p>Tally has user-level security but granular role design — "salesman in branch B can see only their leads, cannot edit prices, cannot delete vouchers, must get manager approval above ₹50,000" — gets unwieldy at scale.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cmp-card">
      <div class="cmp-ic" style="background:var(--purple-bg);color:var(--purple)"><i class="fa-solid fa-clipboard-check"></i></div>
      <h3>Industry-Specific Compliance</h3>
      <p>BIS lot-stamping for steel, IATF traceability in automotive, GMP records for pharma and food, FSSAI batch records — these have specific data and audit-trail formats Tally does not produce natively.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cmp-section" style="background:var(--bg);max-width:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2>5 Signs You've Outgrown Tally</h2>
    <p class="sub">If three or more of these are true for your business today, the cost of staying on Tally alone is probably higher than a custom ERP investment. We hear these almost weekly from Salem and Coimbatore manufacturers.</p>
    <ol class="cmp-list" role="list">
      <li><strong>You export to Excel for every meaningful report.</strong> Daily collection follow-up, route-wise sales, salesman-wise margin, slow-moving SKUs — if your team's workflow is "export from Tally, then pivot in Excel," you're paying a hidden labour tax every day.</li>
      <li><strong>Salesmen book orders manually then re-key into Tally.</strong> A 20-person field sales team typically loses 2–3 hours per person per day to paper-to-Tally rekeying. That's 40–60 hours per day across the team — equivalent to 5–7 full-time staff doing nothing but data entry.</li>
      <li><strong>Production data lives in WhatsApp Business and Excel, not Tally.</strong> Plant supervisors send daily output on WhatsApp, planners maintain Excel sheets, and Tally only sees the closing stock. Your real production system is WhatsApp + Excel — Tally is just the GST submission layer.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-location stock visibility takes a phone call.</strong> "How much HR coil do we have at Branch B right now?" should not require calling the warehouse manager. If branch heads phone each other to plan dispatches, your stock system is operating on faith, not data.</li>
      <li><strong>You're paying for 3+ Tally licenses + 2 add-ons + a customisation partner.</strong> Once your annual Tally + add-on + customisation spend crosses ₹2–3 lakh, the gap to a custom ERP build narrows quickly — and a custom ERP gives you source code IP, not perpetual licensing.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

