<section class="cmp-section">
  <h2>Migration Strategy — How to Move Off Tally Without Disruption</h2>
  <p class="sub">A 6-step migration plan refined over multiple Salem and Coimbatore manufacturer migrations. The key principle: never cut over without a parallel run. The second key principle: keep Tally Prime as a read-only archive even after cutover.</p>
  <div style="border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;padding:22px;background:var(--white);margin-top:18px">
    <div class="cmp-step"><div class="num">1</div><div class="body"><h3>Audit & Scope (2 weeks)</h3><p>We sit with your operations, sales, and accounts teams to map every Tally Prime workflow, every Excel sheet, every WhatsApp Business chat that holds business data. Output: a precise scope document and master list of pain points.</p></div></div>
    <div class="cmp-step"><div class="num">2</div><div class="body"><h3>Custom Build (3–5 months)</h3><p>Iterative development with weekly demos. We build modules in priority order — usually sales/billing first (replaces Tally invoicing), then inventory and purchase, then production, then mobile. Accountants see Tally-like voucher screens, so the muscle memory transfers.</p></div></div>
    <div class="cmp-step"><div class="num">3</div><div class="body"><h3>Master Data Migration (4–6 weeks)</h3><p>Ledgers, items, parties, GST numbers, opening balances, price lists, BOM data — all migrated via Tally XML export, validated, and reconciled. Your CA signs off on opening balances before we move to live data.</p></div></div>
    <div class="cmp-step"><div class="num">4</div><div class="body"><h3>Parallel Run (2 months)</h3><p>Both systems run simultaneously. Vouchers entered in both, daily reconciliation. Discrepancies are caught while Tally Prime is still authoritative. We do not cut over until 30 consecutive days of zero variance.</p></div></div>
    <div class="cmp-step"><div class="num">5</div><div class="body"><h3>Cutover (1 week)</h3><p>Custom ERP becomes the system of record. Tally Prime moves to read-only mode for the new financial year. Your CA continues filing returns from the new system, with Tally available for reference. We run a 24/7 support window for 2 weeks post-cutover.</p></div></div>
    <div class="cmp-step"><div class="num">6</div><div class="body"><h3>Tally Archive for Past Years</h3><p>Your existing Tally Prime company file stays preserved as a read-only historical archive for 7+ years (statutory minimum). Past returns, audits, and historical queries are answered from the Tally archive. New transactions all happen in the custom ERP. Best of both worlds.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <p style="margin-top:18px"><strong>Detailed migration playbook:</strong> Read our <a href="/../blog/tally-to-cloud-migration.html">Tally migration playbook</a> and the broader <a href="/../blog/custom-erp-vs-readymade.html">custom ERP vs readymade comparison</a> for deeper context.</p>
</section>

<section class="cmp-section" style="background:var(--bg);max-width:none;padding-left:0;padding-right:0">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2>What If You Just Need to ENHANCE Tally?</h2>
    <p class="sub">Honest alternative path — and often the smartest. You don't have to leave Tally Prime to fix your workflow gaps.</p>
    <div class="cmp-callout">
      <h3>Keep Tally as the accounting backbone, build custom modules around it</h3>
      <p>For many mid-market SMEs, the right answer is not "replace Tally" — it's "keep Tally, extend Tally." We build custom modules — sales mobile app, production tracker, multi-branch stock dashboard, WhatsApp Business order intake, customer portal — that sync with Tally Prime via XML, ODBC, or Tally Connector. Your accountants keep using Tally exactly as before. Operations and sales teams move to purpose-built apps. Data flows two ways automatically.</p>
    </div>
    <h3>What this looks like in practice</h3>
    <p>A typical setup: sales app on mobile pushes orders to a custom backend, which posts sales vouchers into Tally via XML at end of day. Production tracker captures shop-floor output and posts stock journal entries to Tally. WhatsApp Business reminders are sent automatically when Tally shows pending bills above 30 days. Tally remains the single source of accounting truth — but the daily operational reality of 50 people now happens in tools designed for them.</p>
    <h3>When this is the right choice</h3>
    <p>Choose this hybrid path if (a) your accountants and CAs are deeply tied to Tally and would resist a full migration, (b) your statutory and audit setup is mature and you don't want to disturb it, (c) your real pain is in sales, production, or mobile — not in accounting itself. Cost is typically ₹6–12 lakh for a focused module instead of ₹15–30 lakh for a full ERP — and you preserve everything that already works.</p>
    <h3>When this is NOT enough</h3>
    <p>If you have 4+ branches with multi-GSTIN, 50+ users, and need genuine multi-branch real-time consolidation with role-based dashboards, the hybrid approach hits its own ceiling. At that scale, a unified custom ERP is usually the right call. Either way, we'll tell you honestly which path fits — book a free 30-minute scoping call and we'll map your specific situation.</p>
