<section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px">
    <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="faq-sub">Common questions buyers ask when comparing Tally Prime against custom ERP.</p>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Is Tally bad for Indian SMEs?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">No. Tally Prime is excellent for accounting, GST returns, and statutory compliance — it is used by 2+ million Indian businesses for very good reason. The question is not whether Tally is bad, it is whether Tally still fits your workflow as you scale beyond accounting into manufacturing, multi-branch operations, mobile sales, marketplace selling, or 50+ users with role-based workflows. Most SMEs outgrow Tally for those scenarios, not for accounting itself. If your business profile fits within Tally's design intent, stay on Tally — we'll tell you that honestly.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>When should I switch from Tally?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Consider switching when at least 3 of these are true: (1) you export to Excel for every meaningful report, (2) salesmen book orders manually then re-key into Tally, (3) production data lives in WhatsApp Business chats and Excel, (4) multi-location stock visibility takes a phone call, (5) you are paying for 3+ Tally licenses plus 2+ third-party add-ons. These signals tell you that workflow gaps now cost more in daily friction than a custom ERP investment would cost over 3 years.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can I keep Tally for accounting and add custom modules around it?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes — and this is often the smartest path. Keep Tally Prime as your accounting and statutory backbone, and add custom modules for your real workflow gaps: a sales mobile app, production tracker, multi-branch stock dashboard, or a WhatsApp Business order intake portal. These modules sync data with Tally via XML, ODBC, or Tally Connector. You preserve your CA workflow and migrate only the parts that actually hurt. Cost is typically ₹6–12 lakh for focused modules vs ₹15–30 lakh for a full ERP replacement.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How long does Tally to ERP migration take?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">For a typical mid-market SME: 3–5 months for the build, 4–6 weeks for master data migration, 2–3 months for parallel run, and 1 week for cutover. End-to-end roughly 6–9 months. We always insist on a parallel run of at least 2 months — both systems live, daily reconciliation — before declaring the new ERP authoritative. Cutover only happens after 30 consecutive days of zero variance between Tally and the new system.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What happens to my historical Tally data?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Two options. Option 1 (most common): keep your existing Tally Prime company data file as a read-only archive for 7+ years of historical access — it stays available for past returns, audits, and reference queries. Option 2: import opening balances, masters, and last 1–2 financial years into the custom ERP. We typically recommend a hybrid — archive Tally for past financial years, import current-year opening balances into the new ERP. Your statutory archive remains untouched and inspectable.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How much does Tally migration cost?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Migration scope drives cost. Master data migration alone is typically ₹50,000–₹1,50,000. A full custom ERP build with Tally migration starts around ₹15 lakh and ranges to ₹30+ lakh for multi-branch, multi-module deployments with mobile apps and integrations. The hybrid path — keep Tally, add custom modules — is typically ₹6–12 lakh for the modules. The 3-year TCO including AMC is generally 30–50% lower than equivalent SaaS ERP for mid-market businesses. See our <a href="/../pricing/custom-erp-cost-india.html">custom ERP cost guide</a> for detailed pricing.</div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Will my CAs and accountants need to relearn?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">There is a learning curve, but a well-built custom ERP can replicate Tally Prime-style accounting screens — voucher entry, day book, ledger view, trial balance — so accountants stay productive quickly. If you choose the hybrid keep-Tally-add-modules path, accountants continue using Tally Prime exactly as before, and only operations and sales teams move to the new system — zero retraining for accounts. Most CAs adapt within 2–4 weeks of training when full migration is chosen, and we provide ongoing support during the transition.</div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

